![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1585163748796-FLTVWV0X7KJJ4GBN52FJ/119.jpg?format=original)

The character of Robin aka Dick Grayson, who first graced comic books in 1940, is officially 80 years old! To celebrate, DC put out a [**Robin 80th Anniversary 100 Page Super Spectacular**](https://www.dccomics.com/graphic-novels/robin-80th-anniversary-100-page-super-spectacular-1)! In it, is a fond look back at every person to pick up the mantle of Robin from Dick's replacement Jason Todd, to Tim Drake, a bit of Stephanie Brown, and even some stories following the current Robin, Damian Wayne! Join us in this touching retrospective of 80 years of The Boy Wonder, one half of the Dynamic Duo, the right hand of the Dark Knight himself, Robin!   
  
If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](/comicbookclique/episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
